This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring the third Saturday of each May as Armed Forces Day. The proclamation pays tribute to the service and sacrifices of the men and women in the Armed Forces, highlighting their courage, dedication, and the values they embody. It also emphasizes the importance of supporting the families of service members and encourages Americans to learn more about military service and volunteer to support the troops. The proclamation supersedes a previous proclamation from 2011.